Binance Wallet is launching two exclusive campaigns with Mitosis:

  1. Booster Campaign: Share in a prize pool of 1.5% MITO total token supply by completing phased tasks and supporting the project during its early development phase.

  • Booster Campaign Season 1: $1,000,000 in MITO (Mitosis tokens)
  • Booster Campaign Season 2: To be announced at a later stage.

  1. TGE Campaign: Eligible users can subscribe to Mitosis’s utility token, MITO, before it becomes tradable.
Binance Wallet Booster Campaign
Please note: In compliance with MiCA regulations, the Simple Yield Mitosis USDT vault and related USDT deposit activities are not available to users within the European Economic Area (EEA).

Promotion B: Deposit a minimum of 0.03 BNB in Simple Yield Mitosis BNB vault to share $400,000 of MITO rewards for 7 days!
Activity Period: 2025-08-19 00:00:00 to 2025-08-25 23:59:59 (UTC)

During the promotion period, all eligible users who deposit at least 0.03 BNB in Simple Yield Mitosis BNB vault via Binance Wallet Earn can share in a total boosted APR reward pool of $400,000 in MITO. The daily reward pool is $57,142.85.

Notes:
  • APR (Annual Percentage Rate) is calculated based on the TVL (Total Value Locked) and updated hourly.
  • Historical APR doesn't refer to future returns and is for reference only.
  • Individual daily rewards are calculated based on the proportion of their assets relative to the total amount in the Binance wallet.
  • The maximum duration of staking for promotion is 7 days and the daily reward pool is $57,142.85.
    For example, if a user stakes 1 BNB and the daily TVL growth in the promoted pool on Binance Wallet is 100 BNB, the daily prize pool is $57,142.85., the user’s estimated daily reward will be: 1 BNB ÷ 100 BNB x $57,142.85 = $571.42 in MITO

Binance Wallet Exclusive TGE Campaign
During the Binance Wallet Exclusive TGE Campaign, users can subscribe to Mitosis’s utility token, MITO, exclusively within the Binance Wallet. The subscription process follows an over-subscription model, allowing up to 3 BNB deposits per user. Token allocation is proportional to the total BNB deposited by all participants.

After the subscription period ends, users can claim their MITO tokens via the [Assets] tab, with unused BNB automatically refunded.

Important: TGE tokens will NOT be available for trading until the subscription period ends. Any TGE tokens in public circulation before this time are fraudulent. Please confirm the TGE contract address from the official TGE Project channel before making any trades.

How to Participate:
  1. Update your Binance App to the latest version, and ensure you have sufficient BNB and Alpha Points balances in your Binance backed-up Keyless Wallet;
  2. Visit Binance Wallet, tap on the Mitosis’s activity banner and follow the instructions to participate during the subscription period.

Subscription Details
  • TGE Token: Mitosis(MITO)
  • Chain: BNB Smart Chain
  • Total Raise Amount: $200,000 in BNB
  • Available Token: 10,000,000 MITO (1% of the total supply)
  • Accepted Token: BNB
  • Price per Token: $0.02 USD in BNB
  • Subscription Cap per Binance Wallet user: 3 BNB
  • Binance users who have sufficient Binance Alpha Points can join the TGE event through the Alpha event page. Participation in this TGE event will deduct 15 points.
  • Allocation: based on a pro-rata basis of a user’s subscription amount against the total amount deposited during the subscription period.
  • DEX Trading Date: Available for trading on Binance Wallet DEX after the subscription period ends.
  • For your asset’s security, always verify the official contract address through Mitosis’s official channels before making any transactions.

    For projects interested in similar opportunities, apply here.
Binance Wallet Exclusive TGE Timeline
Phase 1: BNB Deposit Subscription Eligible users may participate by depositing up to 3 BNB during the Subscription Period. Users should ensure their deposits do not exceed the maximum individual cap.

Phase 2: Token Allocation Upon subscription completion, users will be able to claim their allocated tokens based on the final calculation. Please confirm the token contract address from the official TGE Project channel before making any trades.

Phase 3: Trading Opens on Binance Alpha Once the token is officially live after the subscription period, users will be able to freely trade their allocated tokens on Binance Alpha.

Note:
  • The Binance Wallet Exclusive TGE event start date and Alpha Points requirement will be announced on the official Binance Wallet X soon.
  • For security reasons, always verify the official contract address through Mitosis’ official channels before making any transactions.

Important Reminder
  • TGE tokens will NOT be available for trading until the subscription period ends. Any TGE tokens in circulation before this time are fraudulent. Please confirm the TGE contract address from the official TGE Project channel before making any trades.
  • Please check your Binance Alpha points on the Binance App to ensure you are eligible. Learn how on this FAQ page.
  • Allocations are determined on a pro-rata basis, based on the total amount deposited during the subscription period.
  • You will be able to claim your allocation and unused funds once the subscription period ends.
Mitosis Overview
Mitosis is an L1 network designed for programmable liquidity that redefines the liquidity provision experience for both DeFi projects and liquidity providers. The protocol aims to solve problems and inefficiencies arising from the lack of price discovery and fair market pricing of liquidity in DeFi applications.

Website: https://mitosis.org/
X: https://x.com/MitosisOrg
Token Overview
  • Token Name: Mitosis
  • Ticker: MITO
  • Chain: BNB Chain and Mitosis Chain (EVM)
  • Total Token Supply: 1,000,000,000
  • Token Utility:
    • Native gas token for all Mitosis Chain transactions and smart contract executions.
    • Staking rewards through validator consensus participation.
    • Token gated access for exclusive yield opportunities with preferential terms.
    • Key currency for Mitosis EVM layer to unlock capital-efficient DeFi strategies.
    • Governance participation for deciding key parameters for Mitosis.

  1. Only users who complete the requirements above and deposit selected assets into the promoted pool and hold the miBNB or maUSDT(Lista) for at least 1 hour will be eligible for rewards.

  3. Participants may join one or multiple Booster Campaign activities, depending on eligibility, regional availability, and Alpha Point balance.
  4. Only deposits worth at least 0.03 BNB or at least 25 USDT on BNB chain in the Binance Wallet - [Earn] - [Simple Yield] - [Mitosis] vaults during the campaign period will be considered in the reward calculations.
  5. Users are able to redeem their BNB or USDT on Mitosis DApp. Please note that BNB redemption may take up to 10 days, and USDT redemption may take up to 5 days to complete. For more information, please follow Mitosis’s official Discord.
  6. Participants in Promotion B or Promotion C will automatically participate in Promotion A.
  7. The estimated reward shown in the Simple Yield Mitosis vaults’ page is for reference only and may differ from actual rewards. They do not guarantee future returns and are subject to change.
  8. The TGE token subscription price will be determined based on the BNB opening price one day before the announcement is made. The actual price you pay may differ from the real-time BNB price at the time of your subscription.
  9. 1.5% of Mitosis’s MITO total token supply, allocated to the Booster Campaign, will be distributed in batches during the future campaigns.
  10. Binance will use the average MITO/USD exchange rate during the first 24 hours of trading for reward distribution. The rewards will be distributed on BNB Chain on the Mitosis TGE date, the remaining distributed on the second day of trading if the 5M MITO distributed on the TGE date is below the value of $1,000,000. You can view your reward history in the Binance Wallet by navigating to Discover > Airdrop Zone > Rewards > Details.
  11. For your assets security, always verify the official contract address through Mitosis official channels before making any transactions.
  12. The success of the TGE subscription process depends on the operational capabilities of both the blockchain and the project. In the event that the subscription does not go through, Binance holds no responsibility for the outcome or any gas fees incurred.

Please make sure you are aware of the lock-up period and accompanied risks which apply to tokens in Booster Campaigns. Read the terms and conditions and our FAQs below for more information.
  14. Binance Wallet and the hosting project reserve the right to disqualify a user’s reward eligibility if the account is considered to be involved in any dishonest behavior (e.g.money laundering, wash trading, bulk account registrations/logins, self dealing, or market manipulation). Rewards will not be distributed to users who delete or deactivate their Binance Wallets.
  15. The total allocation pool for this activity is inclusive of all network and gas fees that may incur during the distribution of tokens.

Privacy Preference Center

We use cookies to collect data which improves your experience while you navigate through the website. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. The information does not usually directly identify you but it might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to improve the site making the site work as you expect it to whilst giving you a personalised experience. Of course, we do all this with your consent and in complete transparency. The cookies that are categorized as "Strictly Necessary" are on by default and are stored on your browser as they are essential for the working of basic functionalities and security of the website. You can choose to enable or disable some or all of the additional cookies if they are present, but disabling some of them may affect your browsing experience.
Cookie Policy

Manage Consent Preferences

Strictly Necessary Cookies

Always Active

These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.

Functional Cookies

These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages. If you do not allow these cookies then some or all of these services may not function properly.

Targeting Cookies

Targeting cookies may be set through our site by ourselves and our advertising partners. First parties and third parties will use them to build a profile of your interests based on the browsing information they collect from you, which includes uniquely identifying your browser and terminal equipment. If you do not allow these cookies you will still see basic advertising on your browser that is generic and not based on your interests

Performance Cookies

These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site. All information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous. If you do not allow these cookies we will not know when you have visited our site, and will not be able to monitor its performance.
